sub_title: Project Officer at Faculty of Geo-Information Science and Earth Observation (ITC) of the University of Twente
summary:
Diana Chavarro-Rincón is an international consultant in water management, flood modeling, catchment hydrology and GIS/­­RS applications for the water sector. In 2013 she founded Ambient Sensing and worked as an independent consultant. Her longstanding professional experience spans research, training and projects in South America, Africa and Europe. In 2019 she joined the Faculty ITC of the University of Twente as a project officer for the department of Water Resources.
